Notes:

Date:  0/0/1947
Source:  For the Rest of Our Lives
Author:  DAVIN
Vol / Page:  147
Edition:
Quote:   They drove back along the [Maadi] camp road and up on to Bludger's Hill where the Base Staff dwelt, aloof. First the MS, inscrutable but cordial. Then the Pay Office ... `The working class can kiss my arse, I've got a bludger's job at last', sang Smithy to the tune of the Red Flag. ... `All the boys sing it whenever they pass Bludger's Hill. ... Makes the base-wallahs mad.'
